    <text>
        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Tamás Szalaházy to Miklós Oláh (Bratislava, 31 May 1532)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. He has received the gift, he has read the book and
                            cannot praise it enough; he cannot wait for him to send the finished
                            version. He has already sent the tax from Tapolca to him, but Péter
                            Koczka has captured the messenger. The Bebek brothers have defected to
                            King John I and attacked Tapolca; the famulus of Péter Horváth was
                            killed, the others were captured. 2. He is sending a copy of the letter
                            with which they are enticing the Queen’s followers over to their side.
                            He is toiling away with Bálint Török and László Móré for Oláh’s estates,
                            but in vain. He will find out the rest from the letter to the Queen.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="15320531_2_1.jpg"/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Idem Nicolao Olao salutem.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Litteras vestras<note xml:id="note.1">The last letter by Oláh
                        to Szalaházy we know of is Ep. 213, but there is no word about a gift or
                        book in it.<ref>olahus.tei.15320219_1</ref></note> una cum munere accepimus;
                    legimus libellum, quantum per occupationes licuit, non possumus non laudare opus
                    pii et eruditi viri, sive is interpres sit, sive paraphrastes. Non dubitamus,
                    quin reliquum quoque perfecerit. Rogamus, ut illud quoque quamprimum licuerit,
                    ad nos mittatis. Pensionem abbatiae de <placeName>Thapolcza</placeName><note
                        xml:id="note.2">About the parish of Miskolc, see Ep. 148. Note
                            2.<ref>olahus.tei.15310512_1</ref></note> dudum vobis misissemus,<note
                        xml:id="note.3">Ep. 222.<ref>olahus.tei.15320505_1</ref></note> sed ea
                    pecunia una cum aliis, quae nobis per nuntios civitatum afferebantur, per
                        <persName>Koczka</persName><note xml:id="note.4">Péter Koczka.</note>
                    intercepta est, qui et hodie nuntios ipsos captos tenet. Dabimus tamen operam,
                    ut eam quamprimum aliunde paremus et vobis mittamus.
                        <persName>Emericus</persName> et <persName>Franciscus Bebek</persName><note
                        xml:id="note.5">Imre and Ferenc Bebek, see Ep. 102. Note
                            1.<ref>olahus.tei.15301020_1</ref></note> ad
                        <persName>Ioannem</persName> desciverunt, qui abbatiam de
                        <placeName>Thapolcza</placeName> invadentes eam expugnaverunt, famulum
                        <persName>Petri Horwat</persName>,<note xml:id="note.6">We do not know him
                        more closely.</note> qui ceteris praeerat, crudeli morte affecerunt,
                    reliquos vero, qui illic fuerunt, captivarunt, hinc orsi praeclara sua facinora
                    homines fortissimi.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[2.] Misimus vobis exemplum litterarum, quibus fideles regiae
                    maiestatis seducere conantur, ostendatis illud serenissimae dominae reginae. Pro
                    bonis Dominationis Vestrae et apud dominum <persName>Valentinum
                        Therek</persName><note xml:id="note.7">Bálint Török.</note> et apud dominum
                        <persName>Ladislaum More</persName><note xml:id="note.8">László Móré.</note>
                    multum laboravimus, sed nihil efficere potuimus, non videntur <del
                        corresp="Olahus?">adhuc</del> posse adduci, ut ea remittant, nisi rex cum
                    exercitu veniat. Nostris quoque bonis nihil parcitum est, quae quamvis non sint
                    occupata, tamen ita sunt depraedata et despoliata, ut expedierit ea fuisse
                    occupata. Ceterum suadere Dominationi Vestrae non possumus, ut nunc in his
                    tempestatibus redeat, <choice>
                        <orig>exspectat</orig>
                        <supplied>exspectet</supplied>
                    </choice> per hanc aestatem, quem finem res nostrae sortiturae sint. Deinde, si
                    cum bona venia serenissimae dominae regiae fieri poterit, non improbamus, ut
                    veniat et reginae maiestati serviat, nostra officia non sunt defutura
                    Dominationi Vestrae, quam bene valere optamus. Quae hic habentur, ex litteris
                    serenissimae reginae Dominatio Vestra cognoscet.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"><placeName>Posonii</placeName> ultima Maii 1532.</p>
            </div>
